MAPE¶

In [51]:
def mean_abolute_percentage_error(df, x='x', x_sma='x_sma'):
    return (abs((df[x] - df[x_sma]) / df[x])) * 100


#MAPE for E5, E10 and DIESEL
reference_model['E5_MAPE'] = reference_model.apply(mean_abolute_percentage_error, x='E5', x_sma='E5_SMA', axis=1)
reference_model['E10_MAPE'] = reference_model.apply(mean_abolute_percentage_error, x='E10', x_sma='E10_SMA', axis=1)
reference_model['DIESEL_MAPE'] = reference_model.apply(mean_abolute_percentage_error, x='DIESEL', x_sma='DIESEL_SMA', axis=1)
